Nate over bullhorn:
<i>Sir. Excuse me, sir.</i>

00:10.552 --> 00:14.889
Sir! I need you
to put your hands up
where I can see them.

00:14.973 --> 00:17.726
- ( Joel scoffs )
- Nate: Higher.

00:17.809 --> 00:20.270
- Joel: What the fuck?
- Mm, that's good.

00:20.353 --> 00:24.149
<i>Ma'am, pull his trousers</i>
<i>down around his knees.</i>

00:26.067 --> 00:28.361
- Ah! ( laughing )
- Joel: Nate!

00:28.445 --> 00:31.823
- ( laughs )
-<i> Whoa, what the heck, man?</i>

00:31.906 --> 00:33.450
- Dude!
-<i> ( car door closes )</i>

00:33.533 --> 00:36.578
Joel freaking Hurley.
( laughs )

00:36.661 --> 00:38.997
- Here in Summit, Utah.
- ( laughs )

00:39.080 --> 00:40.373
Come here, man.

00:40.457 --> 00:41.750
- Come here.
- Good to see you.

00:41.833 --> 00:44.627
Man, I never thought
I'd see you here again.

00:44.711 --> 00:48.131
- Well.
- And I'm gonna have
to ask the two of you

00:48.214 --> 00:50.425
to step off
this property,

00:50.508 --> 00:53.386
which is technically
a crime scene.

00:53.470 --> 00:55.305
Which she should know,

00:55.388 --> 00:58.308
'cause I've kind of,
like, told her already
three times.

00:58.391 --> 00:59.809
So, you guys
know each other?

00:59.893 --> 01:01.686
Ah, more or less.

01:01.770 --> 01:03.271
Mostly less.

01:03.354 --> 01:05.940
- But, yeah, if you--
-<i> ( door closes )</i>

01:08.318 --> 01:10.445
- Oh, hey!
- Alan:<i> Hey.</i>

01:10.528 --> 01:11.905
It's all right,
it's all right.

01:11.988 --> 01:15.742
It's just
a nostalgia thing.

01:15.825 --> 01:17.452
You remember
Joel Hurley.

01:17.535 --> 01:19.120
<i>He used to live here.</i>

01:20.413 --> 01:21.706
Looks familiar.

01:21.790 --> 01:24.334
-<i> Alan Pape.</i>
<i>How are you?</i>
- Good.

01:24.417 --> 01:27.253
<i>I assume you folks</i>
<i>saw the yellow tape</i>
<i>bottom of the drive?</i>

01:27.337 --> 01:29.214
Petra:<i> We came,</i>
<i>actually, the other way.</i>
<i>Sorry about that.</i>

01:29.297 --> 01:32.675
You were the detective
in charge four years ago.

01:32.759 --> 01:35.428
- Alan:<i> Do I know you?</i>
- No, we never met.

01:35.512 --> 01:37.889
Nate:
So, guys, both of you,

01:37.972 --> 01:40.225
<i>I need you</i>
<i>off the property now.</i>

01:40.308 --> 01:42.101
Alan:
<i>Yeah, I hate</i>
<i>to be a hard-ass,</i>

01:42.185 --> 01:44.854
<i>but we got press crawling</i>
<i>up out of the ground</i>
<i>like worms.</i>

01:44.938 --> 01:46.523
Folks up on the hill
just trying

01:46.606 --> 01:48.817
to enjoy a modicum
of privacy.

01:50.652 --> 01:52.278
- If you, uh...
- Of course.

01:52.362 --> 01:53.738
Nate:
<i>Alan.</i>

01:59.577 --> 02:01.496
Listen, don't worry
about Alan.

02:01.579 --> 02:03.456
He's just doing
his job.

02:03.540 --> 02:05.875
He knows where
his bread is buttered.

02:05.959 --> 02:09.379
That doesn't
mean it was smart
to bring him up here.

02:09.462 --> 02:11.881
Joel, on a lighter note,

02:11.965 --> 02:15.426
you'll never guess
who I literally just left
to come up here.

02:15.510 --> 02:19.097
- Oh, yeah?
- He's a Virgo,
he hates long lines.

02:19.180 --> 02:22.684
- ( chuckles )
- He loves leisurely walks
in the rain

02:22.767 --> 02:25.186
- and Italian cuisine.
- Huh.

02:25.270 --> 02:27.063
Nate:
Actually, I don't know
if any of those are true.

02:27.146 --> 02:28.857
<i>I don't even know</i>
<i>if he's a Virgo.</i>

02:28.940 --> 02:31.192
-<i> ( chatter )</i>
-<i> ( dishes clanking )</i>

02:35.029 --> 02:37.782
Joel:
No fucking way!
Frank!

02:37.866 --> 02:39.617
- ( laughs ) Ahem.
- Nate: Hey, Frank!

02:39.701 --> 02:42.078
Joel:
Yeah!

02:42.161 --> 02:44.414
( exhales )
Okay. Ahem.

02:44.497 --> 02:45.999
- Hey, buddy!
- Hey, no way!

02:46.082 --> 02:47.542
- No way.
- Look at that beard.

02:47.625 --> 02:50.879
Look who I found
trolling for hookers
by the interchange.

02:50.962 --> 02:52.547
How you guys doing?
You wanna sit down?

02:52.630 --> 02:54.382
- Heck, yeah, we're gonna sit.
- Yeah, sit down.

02:54.465 --> 02:56.509
- ( chuckles )
- Just sitting by yourself?

02:56.593 --> 02:58.094
- Yeah.
- ( both chuckling )

02:58.177 --> 03:01.347
- Oh, Frank, this is Petra.
- Oh, we met a few days ago.

