She's been all over me
about the night in question,

03:04.017 --> 03:05.935
the night we went to
the movies-- "Hobbit 2."

03:06.019 --> 03:08.897
Yeah, at Eastridge.
Not as good as the first.

03:08.980 --> 03:11.524
Seriously,
who names anything
"Desolation of 'Smog'"?

03:11.608 --> 03:14.402
- ( Frank chuckles )
- Nate: Smaug.

03:14.485 --> 03:16.738
- So, how's Laura?
- Joel: She's good.

03:16.821 --> 03:19.407
- Yeah,
it's a really good thing.
- You guys got married.

03:19.490 --> 03:21.200
Said he saw it
on Facebook.

03:21.284 --> 03:24.412
Yeah, we just tried
to keep it small,
just family.

03:24.495 --> 03:26.164
Hey, it's a clean break,
I get that, man.

03:26.247 --> 03:27.665
It was super clear.

03:27.749 --> 03:29.083
Everybody's fine with that.
Don't worry about that.

03:29.167 --> 03:30.585
It's fine.

03:32.170 --> 03:34.380
Well, I'm, uh--
I'm kind of done here.

03:34.464 --> 03:36.049
Joel:
<i>Well, shit.</i>

03:36.132 --> 03:38.092
I'll tell you the great thing
about being manager now--

03:38.176 --> 03:39.469
the benefits
are awesome.

03:39.552 --> 03:42.263
Like, I get to leave
super late

03:42.347 --> 03:44.891
and I get to arrive
super early.

03:44.974 --> 03:47.477
( laughing )

03:47.560 --> 03:49.145
Frank:
<i>How long are you here?</i>
<i>We've gotta hang out.</i>

03:49.228 --> 03:51.814
Just a couple of days.
Yeah, we should definitely
hang out.

03:51.898 --> 03:54.108
<i>You wanna make a plan now?</i>
<i>Should I give you a call or...?</i>

03:54.192 --> 03:55.485
<i>We'll hang out now</i>
<i>if you want to.</i>

03:55.568 --> 03:57.445
<i>Wanna hang out now?</i>
<i>Or not.</i>

03:57.528 --> 03:59.781
-<i> If you're busy,</i>
<i>I can-- whatever.</i>
- Ahem.

03:59.864 --> 04:02.158
<i>Whatever you want is fine.</i>
<i>We don't have to hang out</i>
<i>at all if you're busy.</i>

04:02.241 --> 04:03.576
-<i> I understand.</i>
- No, I'm-- I'm just
a little fried,

04:03.660 --> 04:05.828
but, uh,
you taking off?

04:05.912 --> 04:07.038
Yeah.
You want a ride?

04:07.121 --> 04:08.498
<i>Yeah,</i>
<i>that'd be good.</i>

04:08.581 --> 04:10.458
-<i> That good</i>
<i>with you guys?</i>
- Great.

04:10.541 --> 04:12.502
- Great.
- Frank:<i> Good, yeah!</i>

04:12.585 --> 04:14.253
-<i> I'll give you a ride.</i>
- Like old times.

04:14.337 --> 04:16.422
-<i> Yes, oh, yeah.</i>
- ( both chuckling )

04:18.049 --> 04:20.343
Well, I'll see you guys--
see you guys later.

04:20.426 --> 04:22.387
- Nate:<i> Yeah.</i>
<i>Another day.</i>
- Another day.

04:22.470 --> 04:25.348
Another day.
Let me, uh-- I gotta
settle up here.

04:25.431 --> 04:28.685
<i>And I have a sour</i>
<i>piece of news.</i>

04:28.768 --> 04:31.479
- Nate: Hmm?
- In my car and not
in my pocket is...

04:31.562 --> 04:33.231
-<i> Frank, Frank, come on.</i>
- ...my wallet.

04:33.314 --> 04:34.232
Thank you.

04:36.150 --> 04:38.069
- Get out of here.
- I'll, uh-- I'll text you
tomorrow.

04:38.152 --> 04:39.487
- Great.
- ( clears throat )

04:39.570 --> 04:41.406
- Joel: Man.
- Frank: Yeah, I know.

04:41.489 --> 04:45.952
-<i> Get out of town.</i>
-<i> I know, man.</i>
<i>Is this nuts or what?</i>

04:46.035 --> 04:48.621
Frank:
It's been, what,
four, five years now?

04:51.290 --> 04:53.084
Nate:
Frank's subtle.

04:53.167 --> 04:54.335
Mm.

04:55.962 --> 04:59.257
So, what's the deal
with Alan?

05:00.717 --> 05:02.969
Alan? Okay.

05:03.052 --> 05:05.346
Here's what you need
to know about Alan.

05:05.430 --> 05:08.182
30 years,
he worked for
the whole town.

05:08.266 --> 05:10.601
Population: 36,000.

05:10.685 --> 05:12.729
Drove the same
Chevy Malibu.

05:12.812 --> 05:14.439
<i>Last three years,</i>

05:14.522 --> 05:17.567
<i>he has worked</i>
<i>for 12 families</i>

05:17.650 --> 05:19.861
<i>and is on</i>
<i>his second Porsche,</i>

05:19.944 --> 05:23.990
<i>which he just loves</i>
<i>to drive around past us.</i>

05:25.742 --> 05:28.995
I'm glad
you're good, man.

05:29.078 --> 05:31.831
You look like the guy I met
when you first got to town.

05:31.914 --> 05:34.459
( both chuckling )

05:34.542 --> 05:38.546
- Well, my job
is pretty physical.
-<i> Mm-hmm.</i>

05:38.629 --> 05:41.549
<i>A lot of that's the gym,</i>
<i>though, too, isn't it?</i>

05:41.632 --> 05:44.260
<i>Isn't it?</i>
<i>Come on.</i>

05:44.343 --> 05:46.596
- Yeah, I supplement.
-<i> Uh-huh.</i>

05:46.679 --> 05:48.639
<i>But most of it's,</i>
<i>you know, whatever.</i>

05:48.723 --> 05:50.600
Whatever.
( chuckles )

05:50.683 --> 05:53.478
You said you
were working where,
some kind of hunting thing?

05:53.561 --> 05:56.731
Yeah, my uncle
has this, uh--
he has an outfit.

05:56.814 --> 05:58.232
It's-- it's nice.

05:58.316 --> 06:01.027
Uh, yeah.

06:01.110 --> 06:03.446
Clean air.
Nice.

06:03.529 --> 06:06.532
And Laura's working
for a doctor, is that right?

06:06.616 --> 06:08.409
<i>Yeah.</i>

06:08.493 --> 06:09.994
Big contrast.

06:11.996 --> 06:14.248
What are you
getting at with that?

06:14.332 --> 06:17.835
Oh, nothing, nothing.
Just... nothing.

06:17.919 --> 06:20.630
<i>Have you met the guy?</i>
<i>Is he a nice guy, though?</i>

06:20.713 --> 06:22.799
I don't know.
I mean, he flies to Bolivia

06:22.882 --> 06:25.301
and does cleft palates
for free.

06:25.384 --> 06:26.427
<i>Ah.</i>

06:26.511 --> 06:29.472
( chuckles )
So he does boobs and Botox

06:29.555 --> 06:31.891
to pay for his Mercedes,
is that it?

06:31.974 --> 06:34.894
- ( both laughing )
-<i> That sounds about right.</i>

06:34.977 --> 06:37.480
Eh, I don't know
what he drives.

06:37.563 --> 06:40.483
<i>It looks like he had</i>
<i>a very nice Christmas</i>
<i>party, though.</i>

06:43.945 --> 06:45.905
I saw it in a post
Laura did.

06:47.907 --> 06:49.909
<i>Office party,</i>
<i>it looked like.</i>

06:51.202 --> 06:52.537
<i>I didn't</i>
<i>see you in it.</i>

06:54.372 --> 06:55.665
Yeah, I don't know.

06:55.748 --> 06:57.708
I think I had
a work thing or something.

06:59.252 --> 07:00.753
I don't remember.

07:03.381 --> 07:07.552
Look, man, the Laura thing,
it actually is kind of
really great.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.096
<i>The movies thing,</i>
<i>that was--</i>

07:10.179 --> 07:11.347
I get it.

07:11.430 --> 07:12.515
-<i> No, seriously--</i>
- I get it.

07:12.598 --> 07:13.850
I get it.

07:13.933 --> 07:15.685
<i>I didn't</i>
<i>say anything.</i>

07:17.061 --> 07:18.146
<i>We were</i>
<i>at the movies.</i>

07:22.483 --> 07:24.152
Cool.

07:24.235 --> 07:26.320
It's just I never
told Laura about her.

07:28.698 --> 07:30.366
I think
it would kill her.

07:32.243 --> 07:34.162
He said we should
stick to the story.

07:34.245 --> 07:36.080
That they're
two separate events.

07:36.164 --> 07:38.916
That us lying
about the girl has nothing
to do with the murder

07:39.000 --> 07:41.711
and that we didn't even
know about the murder

07:41.794 --> 07:43.296
<i>until after</i>
<i>we made the lie.</i>

07:43.379 --> 07:44.755
<i>So that's</i>
<i>what just happened.</i>

07:44.839 --> 07:47.884
<i>So, yeah.</i>
<i>( exhales )</i>

07:47.967 --> 07:50.052
- What was her name?
- Who?

07:50.136 --> 07:53.723
- The woman he slept with.
- I have no idea.

07:53.806 --> 07:55.725
He slept with a woman,
you picked him up
in the morning,

07:55.808 --> 07:57.894
and he never
told you her name?

07:57.977 --> 08:02.231
Why do girls think all guys
brag about their conquests?

08:02.315 --> 08:04.400
<i>Girls brag</i>
<i>way more than guys do.</i>

08:04.483 --> 08:06.694
<i>They tell each other</i>
<i>everything and they have</i>
<i>zero boundaries.</i>

08:06.777 --> 08:08.696
What about
an address?

08:08.779 --> 08:10.615
Frank, um, the morning
of New Year's,

08:10.698 --> 08:11.908
where did
you get him?

08:11.991 --> 08:13.701
<i>In town.</i>

08:13.784 --> 08:16.162
<i>Across from,</i>
<i>uh, the thing</i>
<i>with the, you know.</i>

08:16.245 --> 08:18.789
Okay, so you don't even
know where she lived.

08:18.873 --> 08:20.458
( sighs )

08:20.541 --> 08:22.168
Did you give her
your job, too?

08:22.251 --> 08:24.170
Or just this particular
investigation?

08:24.253 --> 08:26.088
It's not
an investigation.

08:26.172 --> 08:29.050
It's just
two curious people
asking questions.

08:29.133 --> 08:30.468
Frank,

08:30.551 --> 08:34.639
if you never
heard her name

08:34.722 --> 08:36.098
or saw a person

08:36.182 --> 08:38.267
and you never went
to her apartment,

08:38.351 --> 08:41.646
how do you know
there even was a woman?

08:46.525 --> 08:49.320
Okay.
( sighs )

08:49.403 --> 08:52.240
I want you to tell him
that you told us
about the night,

08:52.323 --> 08:53.824
- about the lie.
-<i> What?</i>

08:53.908 --> 08:56.369
-<i> Why?</i>
- Just do it tomorrow.

08:56.452 --> 08:58.371
I'll see if I can
get a man on it.

08:58.454 --> 09:00.915
- I probably can't, not yet.
- I'll follow him.

09:00.998 --> 09:04.669
- What are you, a team now?
- Frank, seriously, bro.

09:04.752 --> 09:06.963
You lied.

09:07.046 --> 09:09.465
Forget
just to a friend,

09:09.548 --> 09:13.052
but you lied to a friend
who's also a cop.

09:13.135 --> 09:14.971
And I'm trying
to sort through this.

09:16.389 --> 09:17.848
And I need
some space from you

09:17.932 --> 09:20.810
because Joel also
happens to be my friend.

09:22.228 --> 09:24.522
Now, here's what
I want you to do.

09:24.605 --> 09:27.650
I want you
to go to his hotel
in the morning

09:27.733 --> 09:30.653
and tell him
that you told us.

09:32.196 --> 09:33.447
If, after
Frank leaves,

09:33.531 --> 09:36.075
