your car, call me.

09:36.158 --> 09:37.702
Stall him.

09:37.785 --> 09:40.621
Don't do anything
but call me.

09:40.705 --> 09:42.707
<i>How's Melissa?</i>
<i>Melissa's his wife.</i>

09:42.790 --> 09:45.543
They met in middle school.
Her dad's a pastor
at St. Luke's.

09:45.626 --> 09:49.046
What is your problem?

09:50.131 --> 09:52.550
<i>This is ridiculous.</i>

09:52.633 --> 09:56.053
Francis,
I need you to focus.

10:02.268 --> 10:04.312
Nate: Ta-da!

10:04.395 --> 10:05.980
Petra:
Lovely.

10:12.737 --> 10:14.030
Who knocks
at their own house?

10:14.113 --> 10:17.325
I don't know.

10:17.408 --> 10:19.702
It's just, it's--
a little weird

10:19.785 --> 10:22.163
bringing a girl home
to meet your wife.

10:22.246 --> 10:23.789
It's stupid.
I don't know.

10:28.961 --> 10:32.048
Oh, okay.
I get it.

10:33.591 --> 10:36.886
- Hi.
- Melissa:<i> Hi.</i>

10:36.969 --> 10:38.471
And he's going on
and on.

10:38.554 --> 10:40.139
"Don't worry,
she's gorgeous.

10:40.222 --> 10:42.224
There's no way she has
any interest in me."

10:42.308 --> 10:44.393
- ( chuckles )
- And what do you know,
he's right.

10:44.477 --> 10:46.562
- ( chuckles )
- Nate: What can I say?

10:46.645 --> 10:49.857
- You can either finish that
or leave the table.
- I call it like I see it.

10:49.940 --> 10:52.693
Natey told me
about your brother.

10:52.777 --> 10:55.780
- Petra:<i> Mmm.</i>
- I, uh-- I tell her
everything.

10:55.863 --> 10:57.198
Not only is she
my better half,

10:57.281 --> 11:00.743
but she's also
a police officer, so.

11:00.826 --> 11:03.537
You know, everything
stays within the cone.

11:03.621 --> 11:06.290
- Mmm.
- And your dad's away
for life, right?

11:06.374 --> 11:11.670
- He's David Neill?
- My father is David Neill,
yes.

11:11.754 --> 11:13.923
I read about
his arrest.

11:14.006 --> 11:15.800
Yanked him
out of the house
on Christmas Eve.

11:15.883 --> 11:17.551
<i>That must have been</i>

11:17.635 --> 11:20.888
<i>quite a game changer,</i>
<i>family wise.</i>

11:20.971 --> 11:23.891
<i>It was</i>
<i>a significant moment</i>
<i>in my youth.</i>

11:23.974 --> 11:27.269
Hey, eat your vegetables.

11:27.353 --> 11:28.896
<i>And your mom, is she--</i>

11:28.979 --> 11:31.524
<i>She died</i>
<i>a few months ago.</i>

11:31.607 --> 11:34.819
- Oh, she was the lady
who I met back in the day.
-<i> I'm sorry I brought that up.</i>

11:34.902 --> 11:38.572
- Petra:
<i>No, it's fine, trust me.</i>
- Apologies. Sorry.

11:38.656 --> 11:44.245
I guess--
I guess the Neill girls
got all the good genes.

11:44.328 --> 11:46.997
Not so much
with the Neill boys, so.

11:47.081 --> 11:48.457
Something like that.

11:48.541 --> 11:50.459
- ( laughing )
- Nate.

11:50.543 --> 11:52.169
Yeah?

11:52.253 --> 11:54.630
- Oh.
- We'll-- we'll be back
very soon.

11:54.713 --> 11:56.841
We're gonna need
about 15 minutes.

11:56.924 --> 11:58.634
Please sit.
Enjoy your dinner.

11:58.717 --> 12:00.428
We'll be right back, okay?

12:00.511 --> 12:02.138
Morgan?

12:02.221 --> 12:04.473
Official man-of-the-house
hat on, okay?

12:10.229 --> 12:11.772
Why?

12:11.856 --> 12:14.150
She's pretty,
she's smart,
she's funny.

12:14.233 --> 12:15.734
Melissa:
<i>She's lost.</i>

12:15.818 --> 12:17.319
Are you kidding?

12:17.403 --> 12:20.865
She is the most focused,
directed person I've ever met.

12:20.948 --> 12:23.200
<i>Yeah, well,</i>
<i>there you go.</i>

12:26.495 --> 12:29.248
-<i> ( phone ringing )</i>
-<i> It's Alan.</i>

12:32.918 --> 12:35.337
It's 10:45!

