Well, he was worried
about hurting his wife,

28:06.851 --> 28:10.063
so he wanted to make sure
if I talked to someone,

28:10.146 --> 28:13.691
I didn't tell them
we, you know, whatever,

28:13.775 --> 28:15.193
spent the night
together.

28:16.653 --> 28:18.530
So, he was here?

28:18.613 --> 28:21.616
Literally there
passed out on the floor.

28:21.699 --> 28:22.909
All night?

28:25.662 --> 28:28.123
I'm sorry, so you'll
go on the record

28:28.206 --> 28:30.959
saying that you were
with Joel from 10:00
New Year's Eve

28:31.042 --> 28:37.006
until... whatever,
first thing New Year's Day,

28:37.090 --> 28:40.677
and you saw Joel there
the whole time?

28:40.760 --> 28:43.346
God, he was all hung up
on the 10:00 thing, too.

28:43.430 --> 28:44.556
I told him
it was midnight.

28:44.639 --> 28:47.600
Oh, I'm sorry,
say that again.

28:47.684 --> 28:49.561
<i>I picked him up</i>
<i>at midnight.</i>

28:49.644 --> 28:51.938
<i>11:57, actually.</i>

28:52.021 --> 28:56.568
<i>( Nate clears throat )</i>
<i>Um, official hat here.</i>

28:56.651 --> 29:01.698
<i>Tia, it is very important</i>
<i>that you tell the truth</i>
<i>about this.</i>

29:01.781 --> 29:03.616
( scoffs )
It is the truth.

29:03.700 --> 29:05.785
I bail on the party.
He's in the lot.

29:05.869 --> 29:07.745
I'm like, "You were
my ski instructor."

29:07.829 --> 29:10.039
And he's like,
"Yeah, what are you
doing here?"

29:10.123 --> 29:12.667
So, as we're leaving,
we hear people celebrating,

29:12.750 --> 29:14.794
and he's like,
"It's midnight.
We should kiss."

29:14.878 --> 29:18.006
But when I pull over,
he's practically asleep
against the window.

29:18.089 --> 29:19.507
Six minutes later,
we come in,

29:19.591 --> 29:22.177
he throws up on himself
and passes out at 12:08,

29:22.260 --> 29:23.720
which I know
'cause I was like,

29:23.803 --> 29:25.346
"Do I wash his pants?
Do I not?

29:25.430 --> 29:26.598
It's a 22-minute cycle,

29:26.681 --> 29:28.683
and I have to be
at work at 9:00."

29:30.894 --> 29:33.813
<i>This isn't about</i>
<i>protecting his wife, is it?</i>

29:36.149 --> 29:37.817
Nate:
<i>Am I missing anyone?</i>

29:37.901 --> 29:41.196
Petra:
<i>Oh, you know,</i>
<i>put the previous renters.</i>

29:41.279 --> 29:43.490
- Nate:<i> Bakers?</i>
-<i> Bethels.</i>

29:43.573 --> 29:46.451
- Bethels.
-<i> Tom and Rachel.</i>

29:46.534 --> 29:51.164
And also someone called
Dave and Cynthia Warner.

29:51.247 --> 29:54.667
- E-L-S Bethels?
- Yep.

29:54.751 --> 29:57.587
<i>Here's a question for you.</i>

29:57.670 --> 29:59.839
<i>What is a girl like you</i>

29:59.923 --> 30:02.425
<i>who's smart, pretty,</i>
<i>and funny--</i>

30:02.509 --> 30:04.844
- Nate.
-<i> Tired of the question?</i>

30:04.928 --> 30:08.181
No, he just pulled up.
And, yes, tired of the question.

30:11.309 --> 30:12.810
Okay.

30:12.894 --> 30:18.066
Well, Melissa's decided
to make you her new project.

30:18.149 --> 30:21.694
- She has a list.
- Tell her thanks,
but I'm good.

30:23.071 --> 30:24.364
You tell her.

30:29.911 --> 30:32.622
- Petra:<i> So, what exactly?</i>
-<i> ( water running )</i>

30:32.705 --> 30:35.166
Vehicular pursuit.

30:35.250 --> 30:38.586
February 3rd,
three years ago.

30:38.670 --> 30:41.172
It's a Saturday.

30:41.256 --> 30:45.343
Approximately 4:17 p.m.

30:45.426 --> 30:48.846
It was a--
it was an icy day.

30:48.930 --> 30:51.015
<i>You tired</i>
<i>of that question?</i>

30:52.350 --> 30:53.893
No.

30:53.977 --> 30:56.646
It is what it is.

30:56.729 --> 30:59.357
Started off...

30:59.440 --> 31:01.901
the whole
pain-in-the-butt factor

31:01.985 --> 31:04.821
was far outweighed
by the...

31:04.904 --> 31:09.867
oh-my-God-you're-so-good-
to-her factor.

31:09.951 --> 31:11.578
( chuckles )

31:11.661 --> 31:14.247
Then I was like,
"Okay, I get it.

31:14.330 --> 31:15.957
I'm a freaking saint.

31:16.040 --> 31:18.459
Now, when can we get rid

31:18.543 --> 31:20.795
of the race car bunk bed
in the master bedroom?"

31:20.878 --> 31:22.630
( chuckles )

31:22.714 --> 31:26.467
The answer is never.

31:26.551 --> 31:28.219
I can never...

31:29.429 --> 31:32.307
with my wife, I mean.

31:35.727 --> 31:37.103
The toughest part?

31:38.855 --> 31:43.276
Figuring out which kind of
version of nice I gotta be

31:43.359 --> 31:45.236
to not piss her off.

31:45.320 --> 31:47.030
Thank you.

31:47.113 --> 31:48.948
And that pisses me off.

31:50.825 --> 31:54.329
And then it's, like,
what kind of anger

31:54.412 --> 31:56.956
am I allowed to show?

31:57.040 --> 31:59.125
Because if I don't
show any anger

31:59.208 --> 32:03.087
and-- and then she says
that I'm not being honest.

32:03.171 --> 32:06.215
( shudders )
And I'm not.

32:06.299 --> 32:07.550
Hmm.

32:07.634 --> 32:10.345
-<i> ( elevator dings )</i>
- Nate: Okay.

32:22.023 --> 32:23.775
Nate:
<i>With Horacio,</i>
<i>we're looking</i>

32:23.858 --> 32:27.445
<i>at nothing more</i>
<i>than just a rushed frame-up.</i>

32:27.528 --> 32:29.197
<i>We have two dozen people</i>

32:29.280 --> 32:31.824
<i>placing him at a party</i>
<i>at his own house</i>

32:31.908 --> 32:32.992
for the whole night,

32:33.076 --> 32:36.579
so that leads us
to Michael O'Connor.

32:36.663 --> 32:39.123
He owns the property
up the hill.

32:39.207 --> 32:41.084
Ah!

32:41.167 --> 32:43.378
- Glad you're here.
- Hey, Nate.

32:43.461 --> 32:44.379
Glad you could make it.

32:44.462 --> 32:47.215
Now, this guy Michael

32:47.298 --> 32:48.925
<i>was at the party early</i>
<i>with Olivia.</i>

32:49.008 --> 32:52.011
<i>He was laughing with her,</i>
<i>even arm in arm.</i>

32:52.095 --> 32:54.555
<i>But he leaves</i>
<i>for a dinner at 8:20.</i>

32:54.639 --> 32:56.391
<i>But a witness,</i>
<i>Tom Davis,</i>

32:56.474 --> 32:59.268
<i>puts him back at the house</i>
<i>the time of the murder,</i>

32:59.352 --> 33:02.230
<i>corroborated by the fact</i>
<i>that Olivia called his cell,</i>

33:02.313 --> 33:04.982
<i>which tower pings tells us</i>
<i>was at his house.</i>

33:05.066 --> 33:07.527
<i>The witness,</i>
<i>Tom Davis,</i>

33:07.610 --> 33:09.320
<i>heard Michael's end</i>
<i>of the call.</i>

33:09.404 --> 33:11.531
<i>Olivia was complaining</i>
<i>about the men in her life,</i>

33:11.614 --> 33:13.700
<i>the same as the call</i>
<i>that she made to JC,</i>

33:13.783 --> 33:16.661
her friend,
immediately afterwards.

33:16.744 --> 33:19.455
Mr. O'Connor
then leaves the next day
for Turks and Caicos.

33:19.539 --> 33:22.709
- Joel:
<i>And that's not suspicious?</i>
- Is what suspicious?

33:22.792 --> 33:25.086
He just takes off
to Turks and Caicos?

33:25.169 --> 33:26.671
<i>Oh, no, no,</i>
<i>no, no, no, no.</i>

33:26.754 --> 33:28.756
<i>This guy takes the same trip</i>
<i>every year for 11 years--</i>

33:28.840 --> 33:31.217
<i>same day, same flight.</i>

33:31.300 --> 33:33.136
<i>No, not a suspect.</i>

33:33.219 --> 33:35.430
<i>However,</i>
<i>I know this is touchy,</i>

33:35.513 --> 33:38.516
<i>but we can't--</i>
<i>we can't rule out Eric.</i>

33:40.518 --> 33:44.105
<i>On his hammer</i>
<i>was found her blood,</i>
<i>his prints.</i>

33:44.188 --> 33:45.898
He was redoing her studio.

33:45.982 --> 33:48.776
<i>( hammering )</i>

33:48.860 --> 33:50.194
What are you doing?

33:50.278 --> 33:52.697
Oh, Liv didn't tell you?

33:52.780 --> 33:54.699
This is gonna be
an office now.

33:59.162 --> 34:01.080
Nate:
<i>It was found in his bag.</i>

34:01.164 --> 34:03.416
Petra:
<i>Who puts a murder weapon</i>
<i>in their own bag?</i>

34:03.499 --> 34:05.084
Nate:
<i>Someone in</i>
<i>a rush to leave?</i>

34:05.168 --> 34:07.670
Petra:
<i>Or someone</i>
<i>who's being framed?</i>

34:07.754 --> 34:09.922
<i>Nate, you said</i>
<i>in your own case notes</i>

34:10.006 --> 34:12.049
"Why is Alan
fixated on Eric?"

34:12.133 --> 34:14.510
You didn't-- you didn't
think the case should
close when it did.

34:14.594 --> 34:15.845
Nate:
<i>But we're</i>
<i>getting off track.</i>

34:15.928 --> 34:17.889
<i>Uh, so, we have Eric.</i>

34:17.972 --> 34:19.807
That leads us
to Cameron.

34:19.891 --> 34:23.519
Cameron motive--
the safe?

34:23.603 --> 34:24.937
Probably.

34:25.021 --> 34:26.189
So, check.

34:27.940 --> 34:30.443
<i>Means-- no idea.</i>

34:30.526 --> 34:32.653
<i>Opportunity--</i>
<i>no idea.</i>

34:32.737 --> 34:34.781
<i>Behavior?</i>

34:34.864 --> 34:36.783
<i>Well, he dropped</i>
<i>off the face of the Earth.</i>

34:36.866 --> 34:40.661
Oh, good work
with the maid's niece.

34:40.745 --> 34:45.416
There was a water bill
that had a forwarding address...

34:45.500 --> 34:48.002
in Langer Plain.

34:48.085 --> 34:51.964
There's a name--
Leticia Aguilar or Letty.

34:52.048 --> 34:54.634
I'm still waiting
to get approval to go in.

34:56.677 --> 34:59.347
- Hey, we'll go.
- No, no, no, I still
need more time.

34:59.430 --> 35:01.432
No, we'll be fine.
We can go right now.

35:01.516 --> 35:03.100
We're not done here.

35:03.184 --> 35:04.852
You were also
on the property.

35:04.936 --> 35:08.105
Well, I worked there
and I lived there,

35:08.189 --> 35:10.942
so of course
I was there.

35:11.025 --> 35:13.736
<i>No, I meant</i>
<i>you were there.</i>

35:13.820 --> 35:15.488
<i>So, did you see</i>
<i>anybody?</i>

35:15.571 --> 35:18.991
<i>Or do you know</i>
<i>anybody who could be</i>
<i>a possible suspect?</i>

35:19.075 --> 35:21.160
<i>When you left</i>
<i>at 9:46,</i>

35:21.244 --> 35:23.538
<i>did you see anyone</i>
<i>on your way out?</i>

35:23.621 --> 35:24.831
We've got a list.

35:24.914 --> 35:26.499
We're just trying
to figure out

35:26.582 --> 35:28.835
if there was anybody
who owed her money

35:28.918 --> 35:31.879
or had beefs
or anything.

35:31.963 --> 35:34.340
Well, I'll put
some thought into it.

35:34.423 --> 35:36.592
She pissed
a lot of people off, so.

35:37.677 --> 35:39.053
Can we talk about Ilsa?

35:39.136 --> 35:42.265
Or whatever
her name is.
Sure.

35:42.348 --> 35:44.517
<i>So, uh,</i>

35:44.600 --> 35:47.478
<i>there's no easy way</i>
<i>to say this,</i>

35:47.562 --> 35:49.021
<i>so I just will.</i>

35:51.607 --> 35:54.694
<i>I'm in</i>
<i>a weird place here.</i>

35:54.777 --> 35:56.696
<i>Frank told me</i>
<i>about your concerns,</i>

35:56.779 --> 36:00.867
<i>and, um, I'm not gonna</i>
<i>say anything to Laura.</i>

36:00.950 --> 36:04.745
<i>I believe that's between</i>
<i>you two to, um--</i>

36:04.829 --> 36:06.873
<i>whatever,</i>
<i>to work out.</i>

36:09.542 --> 36:11.878
But there's nothing else,
though, is there?

36:13.004 --> 36:14.005
Nothing else what?

36:15.339 --> 36:17.133
<i>That I need</i>
<i>to know about, Joel.</i>

36:22.597 --> 36:23.472
No.

36:25.850 --> 36:27.310
<i>( sighs )</i>

36:27.393 --> 36:30.605
<i>Okay.</i>
<i>Okay, cool.</i>

36:30.688 --> 36:33.900
- You sure?
- ( chuckles ) Yeah.

36:33.983 --> 36:36.485
( chuckles )
Okay.

36:36.569 --> 36:38.738
Okay,
to Leticia's.

36:38.821 --> 36:39.947
Great.

36:42.199 --> 36:43.451
<i>( phone chimes )</i>

36:47.288 --> 36:48.581
<i>( phone chimes )</i>

36:50.374 --> 36:51.751
<i>( phone chimes )</i>

36:55.880 --> 36:57.506
<i>( phone chimes )</i>

36:57.590 --> 37:01.010
Oh, hey, Nate wanted me
to ask you a question.

37:02.303 --> 37:04.388
<i>JC said you owed her.</i>

37:06.891 --> 37:08.935
I don't follow.

37:09.018 --> 37:10.978
<i>Well, we were</i>
<i>talking about</i>

37:11.062 --> 37:13.105
<i>people who owed her money</i>
<i>back at the hotel,</i>

37:13.189 --> 37:15.983
<i>and I just remembered</i>
<i>that JC said that--</i>

37:16.067 --> 37:18.903
Look, tons owed her.
In my case, it was murky.

37:18.986 --> 37:20.613
I mean, when I first
started there,
she was like,

37:20.696 --> 37:22.448
"Hey, you can work
instead of rent."

37:22.531 --> 37:24.659
And then all of a sudden,
she's like, "You owe me
for 10 months."

37:24.742 --> 37:26.118
And I was like, "What?"

37:26.202 --> 37:27.787
But I wouldn't
say I owed.

37:29.956 --> 37:31.707
Oh, you're gonna
turn up here.

37:48.432 --> 37:50.184
( engine turns off )

37:50.268 --> 37:53.270
So, what are you saying?
This is written down
somewhere?

37:53.354 --> 37:56.190
Well, what was written down
is that she was gonna go
into the new year--

37:56.273 --> 37:59.443
she and Eric both-- clean,
without owing or being owed.

37:59.527 --> 38:03.364
<i>And JC said</i>
<i>he found this out</i>
<i>right before Christmas, so.</i>

38:03.447 --> 38:05.992
Anyway, I wouldn't--
I wouldn't worry too much
about it.

38:06.075 --> 38:08.244
Wait.

38:08.327 --> 38:09.412
When?

38:10.746 --> 38:12.331
I just told you,
before Christmas.

38:12.415 --> 38:14.750
<i>No, when did</i>
<i>you hear this?</i>

38:14.834 --> 38:17.253
Various times
over the last week.

38:28.055 --> 38:29.682
Joel:
<i>You and Nate</i>
<i>spoke about this,</i>

38:29.765 --> 38:31.517
<i>and you and JC</i>
<i>spoke about this?</i>

38:31.600 --> 38:33.227
- ( phone chimes )
-<i> I thought you said</i>

38:33.310 --> 38:35.730
<i>you could not get anybody</i>
<i>to talk to you out here?</i>

38:35.813 --> 38:38.607
I said no one<i> wanted</i>
to talk to me.

38:38.691 --> 38:42.111
( phone chiming )

38:45.573 --> 38:46.449
( phone chimes )

38:56.459 --> 38:59.086
- Leticia?
- You're Joel?

38:59.170 --> 39:00.337
<i>Hi, I'm Petra.</i>

39:00.421 --> 39:03.632
- You got a minute?
- Yeah.

39:03.716 --> 39:06.302
Cameron would
constantly blab about
the safe in the lady's studio

39:06.385 --> 39:08.346
and how it was always
keeping cash.

39:08.429 --> 39:10.806
And then he said
there were some art drawings

39:10.890 --> 39:13.476
for her charity,
and he had did research,

39:13.559 --> 39:15.728
- and they were worth $75,000.
-<i> ( phone chimes )</i>

39:15.811 --> 39:18.064
So, then he figured out
the combination to the safe

39:18.147 --> 39:19.565
- and--
- Wait, I'm sorry.

39:19.648 --> 39:22.151
He just figures out
the combination?

39:22.234 --> 39:24.403
In the Sylvester Stallone
movie "Escape Plan,"

39:24.487 --> 39:26.197
they tell which safe numbers
are used the most

39:26.280 --> 39:28.157
- by how dark the keys are.
- ( phone chimes )

39:28.240 --> 39:30.076
And so, he goes
to the studio

39:30.159 --> 39:32.745
and he was like, "Okay,
5 is darkest by a lot,

39:32.828 --> 39:35.081
and then the 7
and the 8."

39:35.164 --> 39:37.458
And so, then he Googles
a whole bunch of stuff,

39:37.541 --> 39:39.043
including her birthday,

39:39.126 --> 39:41.879
which turns out to be
May 7, 1958.

39:41.962 --> 39:43.255
5-7-5-8.

39:43.339 --> 39:45.841
- So then he broke in?
- I don't know.

39:45.925 --> 39:49.595
<i>'Cause then he was gone.</i>
<i>Christmas Eve.</i>

39:49.678 --> 39:52.348
<i>My Aunt Flor was like,</i>
<i>"I told you about him."</i>

39:52.431 --> 39:54.100
Joel:
<i>How did she know him?</i>

39:54.183 --> 39:57.812
I don't know.
They were busybodies,
my aunt and her friends.

39:57.895 --> 40:01.190
She worked for the rich people,
so she thought she was
so important.

40:01.273 --> 40:02.942
Then she left
and she was suddenly

40:03.025 --> 40:05.694
just an old Mexican lady
in Mexico again.

40:05.778 --> 40:09.240
( scoffs )
That's another one
I don't need to bother with.

40:09.323 --> 40:11.075
When did she leave?

40:11.158 --> 40:13.160
Somewhere around
New Year's.

40:13.244 --> 40:16.247
We weren't close.
I wasn't keeping track.

40:16.330 --> 40:18.624
You know
how to reach her?

40:18.707 --> 40:19.875
No.

40:19.959 --> 40:22.670
Anyway, she got married,
moved out of Mexico.

40:22.753 --> 40:24.964
I have no idea what
her last name is now

40:25.047 --> 40:26.841
or what country
she's even in.

40:28.592 --> 40:30.719
Leticia:
<i>What is it that you keep</i>
<i>looking at in there?</i>

40:30.803 --> 40:33.097
Petra:
<i>Is that painting--</i>
<i>by the window,</i>

40:33.180 --> 40:35.266
<i>is that a Xavier Martinez?</i>

40:35.349 --> 40:36.809
Leticia:
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>My uncle had it.</i>

40:38.144 --> 40:39.603
You should
have it looked at.

40:39.687 --> 40:41.313
<i>Why? It's ugly.</i>

40:42.398 --> 40:44.859
How much would you
sell it for?

40:44.942 --> 40:46.944
( sighs )
A hundred dollars?

40:47.027 --> 40:48.571
( laughs )

40:48.654 --> 40:50.114
You should
have it looked at.

40:52.158 --> 40:53.576
Let's go.

40:53.659 --> 40:54.910
Thank you.

41:10.843 --> 41:13.554
Joel:
<i>So, clearly, Cameron</i>
<i>tried to break into the safe.</i>

41:13.637 --> 41:15.598
That's why he cut
the security footage,

41:15.681 --> 41:18.350
and that's probably
why I saw him there
the month before that.

41:18.434 --> 41:21.812
The plan?
Steal it on New Year's
when everyone's distracted.

41:21.896 --> 41:24.190
But she--
she surprises him.

41:24.273 --> 41:26.859
She goes back to the studio
and catches him in the act.

41:26.942 --> 41:28.652
We know that the safe
was banged up.

41:28.736 --> 41:30.487
We know that the money
and the drawings were gone.

41:30.571 --> 41:32.072
I'm-- I'm sorry.

41:32.156 --> 41:34.658
Is it rude of me to ask
why you keep changing
your sunglasses?

41:34.742 --> 41:36.243
Is it a looks thing?

41:36.327 --> 41:37.745
Well, not<i> my</i> looks.

41:37.828 --> 41:39.205
But I like to have
at least some control

41:39.288 --> 41:40.581
over the way things
look around me.

41:40.664 --> 41:42.541
( sighs )

41:42.625 --> 41:45.711
Anyways,
I'm checking with a bunch
of kids' book art dealers,

41:45.794 --> 41:47.588
emailing a bunch
to see if anybody's

41:47.671 --> 41:50.591
ever tried to fence
one of her drawings.

41:50.674 --> 41:52.259
It won't prove anything.

41:52.343 --> 41:54.803
Are you kidding me?
It will prove he
stole them.

41:54.887 --> 41:56.305
We already know
he stole them.

41:56.388 --> 41:58.432
But he was gone
on Christmas.

41:58.515 --> 42:00.684
He left Leticia
on Christmas.

42:00.768 --> 42:02.436
Maybe even made a big show
of doing it, too--

42:02.519 --> 42:04.897
her, the landlord--
so people would think
he was out of town.

42:04.980 --> 42:08.234
Then he just sneaks
back in on New Year's.

42:08.317 --> 42:10.027
The safe had already
been robbed,

42:10.110 --> 42:12.154
which was why it was
empty when the murder
was discovered.

42:12.238 --> 42:14.114
You don't know that.
It could have been
robbed that night.

42:14.198 --> 42:17.326
Why would you break into
a safe you already had
the combination to?

42:28.921 --> 42:30.464
<i>( phone chimes )</i>

42:30.547 --> 42:33.259
<i>( helicopter approaching )</i>

42:37.137 --> 42:39.014
They found a body.

42:39.098 --> 42:41.350
<i>( helicopter whirring )</i>

42:46.146 --> 42:49.984
<i>( chatter )</i>

42:50.067 --> 42:51.819
( camera shutter clicking )

42:55.698 --> 42:57.658
Nope. No.

42:59.034 --> 43:01.203
You cannot
be here, Alan.

43:01.287 --> 43:02.329
Is that her?

43:02.413 --> 43:04.164
Alan, what are you
doing here?

43:04.248 --> 43:07.668
Tom Davis, he runs--
represents the owners
of the property.

43:07.751 --> 43:10.921
I'm aware of who he is,
but right now, this property
is under my jurisdiction.

43:11.005 --> 43:13.507
- We're not going
to get in anybody's way--
- You already are in the way.

43:13.590 --> 43:14.842
Don't you talk to me
that way!

43:14.925 --> 43:16.677
I'm not doing this now.
Dave?

43:16.760 --> 43:18.512
- Tom: Alan, it's all right.
- It's time to go, Mr. Pape.

43:18.596 --> 43:19.972
- Get your hands off me.
- Mr. Pape, it's time to go.

43:20.055 --> 43:23.225
- Tom: Alan...
- Oh, good. No. Nope.

43:23.309 --> 43:24.560
Trust me,

43:24.643 --> 43:26.687
you guys do not want
to be the technicality

43:26.770 --> 43:28.522
that gets this case
shut down again.

43:28.605 --> 43:30.482
Joel:
"Down again"?
You mean it's open?

43:30.566 --> 43:32.651
Nate: Unofficially.
I'm trying to get it
reopened.

43:32.735 --> 43:34.153
And in light
of the new circumstances,

43:34.236 --> 43:35.654
I think I got
a pretty good shot.

43:35.738 --> 43:37.031
Well, that's--
that's great.

43:37.114 --> 43:38.449
Nate:
Yeah, as long
as nobody screws it up

43:38.532 --> 43:40.909
and I get to do the job
the way I need to do it.

43:40.993 --> 43:42.494
Is that why
Alan was so angry?

43:42.578 --> 43:43.954
It's complicated.

43:44.038 --> 43:46.040
Alan is mad because
he's not boss anymore

43:46.123 --> 43:48.625
and because he's trying
to get information that
I can't give him,

43:48.709 --> 43:50.294
- or to anyone!
- Anyone?

43:50.377 --> 43:52.254
Nate:
Yeah, anyone,
meaning specifically

43:52.338 --> 43:54.381
people who are not
involved in this case.

43:54.465 --> 43:56.300
I need you guys
off the property now.

43:56.383 --> 43:58.177
- Reporter:<i> Detective,</i>
<i>a statement, please.</i>
- Joel, please.

43:58.260 --> 44:00.304
Hey! Especially you.

44:00.387 --> 44:02.306
Look, I'm sorry,
but things are
different now.

44:02.389 --> 44:04.391
I-- I can't
communicate with you.

44:04.475 --> 44:07.311
- Are you serious?
- I need you off
the property now.

44:07.394 --> 44:09.313
Reporter:
Is it Olivia Lake?

44:09.396 --> 44:11.106
Would you secure this,
please?

44:11.190 --> 44:12.733
Reporter:
Can you please give us
some more information?

44:12.816 --> 44:14.526
Nate:
No comment.
Come on, Dave, John.

44:14.610 --> 44:18.113
No comment!
Please, no comment.

44:18.197 --> 44:21.033
Um... excuse me, Petra.

44:21.116 --> 44:22.743
I...

44:22.826 --> 44:25.871
think I need to take
a walk or something.

44:25.954 --> 44:28.040
Oh, sure, sure.
Of course.

44:28.123 --> 44:29.875
I gotta--

44:29.958 --> 44:32.002
I gotta think about
some stuff, too.

44:37.091 --> 44:39.009
<i>( helicopter whirring )</i>

44:42.179 --> 44:45.641
<i>( music playing )</i>
